opticsIMEquipmentTable OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX SEQUENCE OF OpticsIMEquipmentEntry
  MAX-ACCESS         not-accessible
  STATUS             current
  DESCRIPTION
    "This table contains the information related to the resources that
     represent the physical components of a managed element, including
     replaceable components. "
::= { opticsIMEqptMibObject 1 }

opticsIMEquipmentEntry OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX     OpticsIMEquipmentEntry
  MAX-ACCESS not-accessible
  STATUS     current
  DESCRIPTION
    "An entry of the equipment table. Each entry (row) corresponds to a
     physical component of a managed element (racks, subracks, slots/boards,
     sub-slots/daughter boards).
     During the commissioning phase the whole set of instances is created by
     the network element itself.

     Each entry may be instantiated or exist without the presence of the
     physical resources. In this case the operationalState will be disabled.
     When the resource is physically removed, the corresponding equipment
     object is not automatically deleted.

     When a resource is physically installed and no corresponding equipment
     object has been created, no self instantiation is performed.

     The equipmentActual attribute represents the type of equipment which is
     physically present  This attribute assume the 'EMPTY' value when either
     the resource is not physically present or the NE is unable to identify
     the equipment type.

     The equipmentExpected attribute contains the type of equipment that the
     managing system expects to be present. It is set by the agent as a side
     effect of setting the equipmentExpectedTypeId associated to.

     The equipmentExpectedTypeId attribute value of each instance may be set
     according to a planned or default configuration known by the NE and
     represents the identifier of the type of equipment expected to be present.

     If no configuration is wanted then the equipmentExpectedTypeId shall be
     set to 0 corresponding to the 'EMPTY' value.

     If the equipmentExpected attribute value is set to a non 'EMPTY' value,
     and if the equipment is not physically present an alarm notification is
     sent with the probableCause of replaceableUnitMissing'.

     When there is a mismatch in the contents of the equipmentActual and the
     equipmentExpected attribute, an alarm notification with probableCause
     'replaceableUnitTypeMismatch' will be raised.

     The equipmentExpected value of 'EMPTY' (no type) does not match any other
     value for equipmentActual except 'EMPTY'.

     In case equipmentExpected is 'EMPTY' and equipmentActual is different from
     'EMPTY' an alarm notification with probableCause
`     'unconfiguredEquipmentPresent' will be raised (exception to mismatch case).

     If the equipmentExpected attribute value is set to 'EMPTY' and the NE is
     not able to identify the resource which is physically present
     (equipmentActual = 'EMPTY'), an alarm notification is raised with
     probableCause 'replaceableUnitProblem'.

     Based on the value of the equipmentExpected attribute, the functional
     objects implemented by the physical instance are automatically created
     inside the NE and are included in the list of the affectedObject pointed
     by the related instance.

     In case equipmentExpected is set to 'EMPTY', no object will be included
     in the affectedObject list.
     When, for reconfiguration purposes, the equipmentExpected attribute is
     changed by the managing system the whole set of functional objects (TPs)
     present in the related list of affectedObjects and associated to the
     previous value of the equipmentExpected are deleted and the new set,
     associated to the new value of equipmentExpected, are created.
     Change of the equipmentExpected of an instance is only permitted when that
     instance is in locked administrativeState and if corresponding functional
     objects can be deleted (e.g. the deletion  should fail if one of these is
     used as a timing reference).
     When a resource is physically removed and replaced by another resource of
     a different type for reconfiguration purposes the new resource can be
     brought into service only after the managing system has changed the
     equipmentExpected value of the corresponding instance matching the new
     equipmentActual value.

     The equipmentAdministrativeState attribute may have the following values:
     locked, and unlocked.
     This attribute reflects  the management authorization for the resource to
     perform its function.
     When an instance enters  the locked administrativeState then all affected
     functional objects enter the disabled operationalState.

     The operationalState attribute may assume two values: enabled and disabled,
     according to the intrinsic capability of the resource to perform its
     function.

     On detection of equipment failures (e.g. replaceableUnitMissing,
     replaceableTypeMismatch, replaceableUnitProblem), the whole set of TPs
     included on the affectedObject list, should change their operationalState
     attribute to 'disabled'. In case of equipment involved in a Equipment
     Protection Switching, the TPs included on the affectedObject list should
     change their operationalState attribute to 'disabled' only for the active
     equipment (not for the stand-by one).
     When an entry of this table enters in disabled operationalState then all
     affected objects enter the disabled operationalState."
  INDEX  { equipmentPosition }
::= { opticsIMEquipmentTable 1 }

OpticsIMEquipmentEntry ::= SEQUENCE {
  equipmentPosition            OCTET STRING,
  equipmentExpectedTypeId      Integer32,
  equipmentExpected            DisplayString,
  equipmentActual              DisplayString,
  equipmentAdministrativeState OpticsIMEqptAdministrativeState,
  equipmentOperationalState    TsdimOperationalState,
  equipmentAsapIndex           Integer32,
  equipmentLabel               DisplayString,
  equipmentBoardReset          Integer32
}

equipmentPosition OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX        OCTET STRING (SIZE(4))
  MAX-ACCESS    not-accessible
  STATUS        current
  DESCRIPTION
    "This object identifies an entry in the equipment table. It identifies the
     position of the equipment (rack, subrack, slot/board and sub-slot/daughter
     board) inside the NE.
     The first octet identifies the rack position, the second the subrack
     contained in the rack, the third the slot/board contained in the subrack
     and the fourth the sub-slot/daughter board contained in the board.
     Octets not significant will be indicated by the value 0 (i.e. the
     position of the second subrack inside the third rack will be identified
     by (3, 2, 0, 0)."
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 1 }

equipmentExpectedTypeId OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX        Integer32
  MAX-ACCESS    read-write
  STATUS        current
  DESCRIPTION
    "This object contains the identifier of the equipment type requested by the
     managing systems. The identifier must be included in one of the entries of
     the opticsIMAllowedEquipmentTypesTable associated to that equipment
     position. As a side effect of setting this object, the agent must set
     the equipmentExpected object with the string associated to this identifier
     (see opticsIMAllowedEquipmentTypesTable)."
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 2 }

equipmentExpected OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX        DisplayString
  MAX-ACCESS    read-only
  STATUS        current
  DESCRIPTION
    "This object contains the equipment type expected by the managing systems.
     It is updated by the agent when the equipmentExpectedTypeId object is set
     by the managing systems."
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 3 }

equipmentActual OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX        DisplayString
  MAX-ACCESS    read-only
  STATUS        current
  DESCRIPTION
    "This object contains the equipment type of the equipment actually present"
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 4 }

equipmentAdministrativeState OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX          OpticsIMEqptAdministrativeState
  MAX-ACCESS      read-write
  STATUS          current
  DESCRIPTION
    "See Textual Conventions."
  DEFVAL { inService }
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 5 }

equipmentOperationalState OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX          TsdimOperationalState
  MAX-ACCESS      read-only
  STATUS          current
  DESCRIPTION
    "See Textual Conventions."
  DEFVAL { enabled }
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 6 }

equipmentAsapIndex OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX          Integer32
  MAX-ACCESS      read-write
  STATUS          current
  DESCRIPTION
    "This object defines the ASAP object associated to the equipment position."
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 7 }

equipmentLabel OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX          DisplayString (SIZE (0..32))
  MAX-ACCESS      read-only
  STATUS          current
  DESCRIPTION
    "This object defines the label associated to the equipment position."
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 8 }

equipmentBoardReset  OBJECT-TYPE
  SYNTAX        Integer32
  MAX-ACCESS      read-write
  STATUS          current
  DESCRIPTION
    "This object defines the board reset command associated to the equipment
     position. The attribute value meaning is product dependant and specified
     within the product specification."
::= { opticsIMEquipmentEntry 9 }

